It should Not allow to SIGN in a new user when Invalid Email OR Password  was provided
It should validate/Sign in user when provided  valid Email/Password
GET /notifications/badge : Verify newly created user notifications badge count should be 0
GET /notifications : Verify newly created user notifications count should be 0
GET /meetups/near-me : Verify newly created user near meetup count should be  >= 0
GET /meetups/user/ : Verify newly created user my meetups count should be 0
GET /groups/user/ : Verify newly created user my groups count should be 0
GET /friends : Verify newly created user Friend's list should be Empty
GET /friends/suggested?page=0&rows=20&lat=31.4205593&lon=74.2786115 : Verify newly created user suggested friends Request should be >=0
POST /meetups - It should create a meetup and return it's ID when provided all required fields.
GET /meetups/:id/counts : Verify user's newly created fistbump has data: { meetupCounts: { members: 0, leaders: 0, host_groups: 0 } }
GET /meetups/user/ : Verify after creating a Fistbump, newly created user my meetups count should be 1
POST /meetups - It should NOT create a Fistbump and return status 400 and exception whith invalid data or Missing required fields.
POST /groups : It should create new group with VALID input fields
GET /groups/new_groupID/members/count : Verify newly created group member count should be 0
GET /groups/new_groupID/candidates : Verify newly created group member candidates count should return 0 (with 0 Members)
GET /groups/new_groupID/meetups : Verify newly created group is NOT a member of any meetup/Fistbump should return 0 Fistbumps
GET /groups/new_groupID/details : Verify that newly created Group details should match new_user_data
PUT /groups : edit previously created group with VALID input fields, should save new information
GET /groups/new_groupID/details : Verify group details after editing group details should match changed_details
GET /groups/{{group_id}}/candidates/remove : fetch list of removable members from newly created group,  should return 0
DELETE /groups/groupID : It should delete previously created group when provided valid group_id
POST /friend/send_to_friend_id/request - It should send friend request to all Users (sandlot_user_[])
Signing-out User#1 after sending friend request to User#2
Sign-in User#2 with valid email
